<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-624-043  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 624 043.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Canadian Datasystems  Oct 1990 v22 n10 p63(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software for the portable office. (guide to choosing software forlaptop computers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Desjardins, Michel.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Users of laptop computers often need word processing capabilitiesin addition to a database, spreadsheets, specialized applicationsand utilities.andP;  The power of the laptop determines whethersoftware designed for the desktop or integrated software should beused.andP;  Integrated software offers multifunction programs that helpsave disk space, create links between and merge modules, andoperate as well as stand-alone programs.andP;  Integrated softwarepackages cost about the same as top-of-the-line single functionprograms and are easier to use.andP;  Many offer word processing,spreadsheets, database and communications applications, andcalculating capabilities.andP;  These include Software Group's Enable,Lotus' Symphony, Innovative Software Inc's Smartware System, andother lower end products.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Laptop ComputersSoftware SelectionWord Processing SoftwareSpreadsheets.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>